# SOLID Architecture for Nuxt

Apply SOLID pragmatically: keep pages thin, logic testable, and dependencies explicit.

## Single Responsibility

One composable or module per concern. Avoid thousand-line SFC scripts.

- Data fetching → `app/composables/useXxx.ts`
- HTTP transport → `app/services/xxxService.ts`
- Pure formatting/mapping → `app/utils/xxxHelpers.ts` or `app/lib/xxxHelpers.ts`
- Page orchestration → one `use<Feature>Page` composable per route

## Open/Closed

Extend via new composables, factory functions, or strategy callbacks instead of editing a large central switch.

## Liskov Substitution

Keep composable return shapes and prop types consistent so callers can swap implementations without changes.

## Interface Segregation

Pass small option objects or focused `ref`s into composables. Never pass the entire page state when only a subset is needed.

## Dependency Inversion

UI and composables depend on abstractions (typed service functions, injectable refs). Call `app/services/` for HTTP — avoid embedding `$fetch` or transport details in presentation helpers.

## Page / Component Structure

```
app/
  pages/
    feature/
      index.vue          ← thin wiring: one composable + template
      components/        ← presentational sub-components (props in, emit out)
        FeatureCard.vue
  composables/
    useFeaturePage.ts    ← orchestrates data, state, and handlers
  services/
    featureService.ts    ← all $fetch / useFetch calls for this feature
  models/
    feature.ts           ← request/response types
```

- Route `index.vue` files should be wiring only: one orchestrator composable and thin SFCs.
- Extract pure formatting/mapping to `*.ts` helpers.
- Extract reactive orchestration to `useXxx` composables.
- Presentational components under `pages/<feature>/components/` receive props and emit events only.
